<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fever1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fever,</orth> subst. a disease characterised by increase of heat and preternatural thirst: <cit><quote>burning --s, agues pale,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 739" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 739</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the raging fire of f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this tyrant f. burns me up,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 3, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a burning f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 56</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fiery f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.270" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 270</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>till the high f. seethe your blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.433" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 433</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. son 147.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 147, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pht 7" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.235" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 235</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.152.74" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.95" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.95" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 95</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 3, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 3, 2</bibl>. Figuratively, == extreme agitation, wild excitement: <cit><quote>in the distraction of this madding f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 119.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 119, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>felt a f. of the mad,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 209</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an envious f. of emulation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 133</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 133</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 133</bibl> <cit><quote>life's fitful f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.2.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 2, 23</bibl></cit>. Denoting a violent shaking: <cit><quote>to make a shaking f. in your walls,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.228" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 228</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>